Description: Sherd of pottery vessel; bird decoration outside. Micaceous orange-brown Nile silt, with a thick red-brown core; thin orange slip on front. Abundant mica and white inclusions. Drill hole for analysis.
Bibliographic references: Schlotzhauer & Villing 2006 / East Greek Pottery from Naukratis: The Current State of Research (p.55 Table 1, p. 65 fig. 42)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IC.055)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 181, Nau 154, pl. 34f-g)
